Moodaley LC(1), Woodward EG, Liu CS, Buckley RJ.

Author information:
(1)Contact Lens and Prostheses Department, Moorfields Eye Hospital, London.

It is observed that few patients over the age of 60 regularly attend the 
keratoconus clinic at Moorfields Eye Hospital. The hypothesis that patients with 
keratoconus have a shorter life expectancy owing to underlying connective tissue 
related disease was tested. From patient records a sample of 337 keratoconus 
